# Lintian overrides for the ReMoM Debian package.
# Installed as /usr/share/lintian/overrides/remom.
# Every entry here must carry a reason -- see doc/#AI_Plans/PRD-Linux-Package-Install.md.

# ReMoMber is installed to /usr/bin, not /usr/games, so lintian's "Section: games
# but nothing in /usr/games" heuristic fires. Deliberate: this package is
# distributed on GitHub Releases rather than through the Debian archive, and
# /usr/bin is on PATH in every environment while /usr/games is only guaranteed on
# desktop installs. Section stays "games" because that is what the package IS.
# Flip the binary to /usr/games and drop this override if we ever target Debian
# proper (see the rejected Tier 3 in BRA-Linux-Package-Install.md).
remom: package-section-games-but-contains-no-game
